properties.Name: Incident
properties.Description:
A distinct event that might have serious consequences, require attention or have reporting requirements associated with it.

This may include major weather events such as Hurricane Katrina or more minor events like a blown transformer.

Columns.Name: IncidentId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Incident.

Columns.Name: IncidentPeriodStartTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp when the incident started.

Columns.Name: IncidentPeriodEndTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp when the incident ended.

Columns.Name: IncidentTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Incident Type.

Columns.Name: LocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Location.

Columns.Name: IssueId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Issue.

Columns.Name: NumberOfInjuries
Columns.Description: The number of injuries that resulted from the incident.

Columns.Name: NumberOfFatalities
Columns.Description: The number of fatalities that resulted from the incident.

Columns.Name: TotalWorkerHoursLost
Columns.Description: The total number of work hours lost as a result of the incident.

Columns.Name: TotalIncidentCost
Columns.Description: The total costs incurred as a result of the incident.

Columns.Name: TotalOutageHoursLost
Columns.Description: The total number of outage hours lost as a result of the incident.

Columns.Name: IncidentPreventableIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates whether the incident was preventable.

Columns.Name: IncidentNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding an Incident.
